---
import PublicLayout from '../../layouts/PublicLayout.astro';
---

<PublicLayout
  title="Getting started — Mnema docs"
  description="A 5-minute tour of Mnema: create a doc, invite a teammate, search, autocomplete, connect Claude."
  pathname="/docs/getting-started"
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 prose-like">
    <a
      href="/docs"
      class="text-xs transition-colors"
      style="color: var(--text-tertiary);"
      onmouseover="this.style.color='var(--text-primary)'"
      onmouseout="this.style.color='var(--text-tertiary)'"
    >
      ← All docs
    </a>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-medium mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">
      Getting started
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm mb-10" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
      A 5-minute tour. By the end, your team has a working doc and Claude can read it.
    </p>

    <ol class="space-y-8 list-none" style="color: var(--text-primary);">
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Create your first doc</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          From <a href="/app">your workspace</a>, click <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">New doc</span>.
          Give it a title. Start typing — Mnema is a live markdown editor. Press
          <code
            class="text-xs px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
            style="background: var(--surface-overlay); color: var(--accent-400);"
          >/</code>
          to insert blocks: headings, code, math, mermaid diagrams.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Invite a teammate</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Open <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">Settings → Members</span> and send an invite by email.
          They get a magic link that lands them straight in the workspace.
          Roles: <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">owner</span> manages billing and people,
          <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">editor</span> writes and comments,
          <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">viewer</span> reads.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Try search</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Hybrid search runs over every doc in the workspace. Search for an exact phrase, a topic,
          or a question. Results rank by both keyword match and semantic similarity — typing
          <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">"rate limiting"</span> surfaces docs about
          throttling even if they don't use the exact phrase.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Use autocomplete</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          As you type, Mnema suggests how a sentence could continue based on the surrounding doc.
          Press <code
            class="text-xs px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
            style="background: var(--surface-overlay); color: var(--accent-400);"
          >Tab</code>
          to accept the suggestion, or just keep typing to dismiss it. Autocomplete is included
          on Pro and Team plans.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Connect Claude</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Open <a href="/docs/connect">Connect to Claude</a> and follow the 30-second setup.
          Once authorized, Claude can search and read your docs as live context — no copy-paste,
          no uploads. Edit a doc and Claude sees the change immediately.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <div
      class="mt-16 p-4 rounded-md"
      style="background: var(--surface-overlay); border: 1px solid var(--border-default);"
    >
      <h3 class="text-sm font-medium mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">
        What's next
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
        Explore <a href="/docs/connect">the connector setup</a>, browse
        <a href="/pricing">the pricing tiers</a> when your team grows past the free limits,
        or just keep writing — Mnema gets out of the way and lets the docs do the work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</PublicLayout>

<style>
  .prose-like a {
    color: var(--accent-400);
  }
  .prose-like a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  ol {
    counter-reset: step;
  }
  .step {
    counter-increment: step;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 2.5rem;
  }
  .step::before {
    content: counter(step);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent-400);
    color: var(--text-inverse);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
</style>
